Tubi: Best New Indie Thriller…….

“SOUTHERN CROSS”: starring MALCOM MCDOWELL, ESAI MORALES AND MICHAEL IRONSIDE. This thriller feature film is finally released to all the major streamer platforms (Amazon /Tubi etc.)

Jim Becket (Writer and director) and John Rodsett produced and shot on location in Chile. 

"Felipe Solano (Malcolm McDowell) is a wealth mine owner in Chile, whose mysterious death opens the door to a life story of danger, collusion and deception. His estranged son, Philip Bergman (Esai Morales) becomes drawn in to the mystery of his father’s death and he becomes embroiled in a conflict with his father’s former partner, Garrison Carver (Michael Ironside). This struggle leads to a dangerous and adventurous flight across the mountains of Chile, to a murderous end."

items.text:
Sichtbare Glaubwürdigkeit vor der Kamera - CHRISTIAN WEISSE 

Speaking Extra | Nebendarsteller | Featured Extra 

in Köln | NRW | deutschlandweit 

Produktionen brauchen nicht immer große Worte, sondern Menschen, die ein Bild tragen. Präsenz, Haltung und Glaubwürdigkeit entscheiden oft darüber, ob eine Szene funktioniert oder nicht. Genau hier positioniere ich mich. Als Speaking Extra, Nebendarsteller und Featured Extra bringe ich Ruhe, Struktur und Authentizität ins Bild, ob in Werbung, Serie, Kino oder Showformaten. 

Ich wirke dort, wo Realität gefragt ist. Institutionelle Rollen, berufliche Kontexte, Alltagsfiguren mit Profil. Kameraerfahren, setdiszipliniert und flexibel einsetzbar, deutschlandweit und zuverlässig. Keine Überzeichnung, kein Theater, sondern glaubhafte Präsenz, die Regie und Casting Sicherheit gibt. 

Du suchst eine sichtbare Nebenrolle oder eine fokussierte Figur mit Wirkung? Dann melde Dich direkt bei mir. 

Kontakt hier per DM oder per e-mail: 

christian.weisse.talent@gmail.com 

Christian Weiße aka Karrideo Imagefilm-Produktion mit freundlichem Hinweis auch die Profile meiner Lebens- und Filmpartnerin anzuschauen: Sandra Wötzel aka Sanny4me aka Sandras Social Media Creation, Redaktion und Moderation 

#SpeakingExtra #FeaturedExtra #Nebendarsteller #CastingDeutschland #FilmUndSerie

# **CASTING CALL(UNPAID)🎬**

I'm a film student directing my second short film titled ***Ohio sucks*** which is an American teen coming-of-age played out in the early 2000s.

I'm looking for a woman in her 40s or who can present as older than their biological age, with an American accent. Ideally also feel comfortable crying on camera. Newcomers are welcome to reach out. Feel free to share this if you have someone in mind. 

**Shoot dates: 6th OR 7th March Berlin📍**

**Role: Supporting lead (A mom role) **

**Compensation: food, drinks, and snacks 🍕**

**Send a message here or email: nora.a@catalyst-students.com**

**My latest short film is on YouTube, you can check it out at @ Jadednorah**

FINAL SHOUT OUT! voicesoftheholocaust.org.uk has had a couple of actors having to pull out of our in person audition day this THURSDAY so a last minute opportunity if you've missed our casting call!

Male aged 18 - 35 for multirole part

National schools tour from Feb 14th through to April / May for the right person. Digs provided

Weekdays only with the exception of Sunday April 12th for a public engagement event in London. 

Equity tier C equivalent rate

Looking for someone who cares deeply about our work as legacy era survivor testimony theatre

Rehearsals in Milton Keynes. Digs provided if needed

Please check our website if interested and email me directly at cate.hollis@voicesoftheholocaust.org.uk for full casting pack

Ta!

✨ **Join Delta Models – Your Gateway to the Spotlight!** ✨

Delta Models is opening doors for fresh talent and established artists alike. We are currently receiving an **incredible amount of castings in both Johannesburg and Cape Town**, and we want YOU to be part of it!

At Delta Models, we pride ourselves on being a professional, forward-thinking agency that connects artists with exciting opportunities across fashion, film, commercials, and events. Whether you’re just starting out or looking to elevate your career, we provide the platform and support to help you shine.

👉 To be considered, simply complete this quick application form: [https://forms.gle/FGsaMjT5EJ2VMs8e7](https://forms.gle/FGsaMjT5EJ2VMs8e7)

🎬 CASTING CALL – VANCOUVER (Festival Short Film)
KAGE (Shadow)

Independent Passion Project

Written & Directed by Erfan Shams

📍 Vancouver

🎥 Psychological / Supernatural / Art-house

💰 Modest honorarium + IMDb credit + reel footage

LOGLINE

Mitch, an obsessive feng shui specialist who cleanses homes contaminated by negative energy, discovers an invisible stain while renovating an old house — a stain that awakens a hidden entity each time he tries to erase it.

PRINCIPAL ROLES

MITCH – Male, late 30s–early 40s (Lead)

Controlled, intelligent feng-shui consultant whose need for order turns into obsession.

Requires precision, restraint, strong internal acting.

LILY – Female, late 20s–30s (Co-Lead)

Grounded, observant assistant who witnesses Mitch’s psychological collapse.

Subtle, emotionally intelligent performance.

HOMEOWNER – Female, 60s (Key Supporting)

Quietly powerful, calm, and authoritative. Gatekeeper of the house.

SUPPORTING / DAY PLAYERS

SERVER – Café scene

VIDEOGRAPHER – Mitch’s crew

CREW MEMBERS (2) – Renovation workers (no dialogue)

CASTING DETAILS

Local Vancouver actors

Non-union welcome

📅 Shoot Dates: February 7 – February 12

📩 Submit headshot + reel to:

Kage@studiosquare.net

☎ +1 (236) 512-3632

**NOWY SERIAL DOKUMENTALNY TRUE CRIME **

**WARSZAWA **

**31.01 / 1.02 / 3.02 / 5.02 **

Do nowego serialu dokumentalnego w formule true crime poszukuję statystów oraz statystów kontynuacyjnych, głównie mężczyzn oraz kilku kobiet wg dat podanych przy konkretnych postaciach.

**Statysta kontynuacyjny 31.01, 1.02 oraz 3.02 (wnętrza):**
* **KRZYSIEK **- mężczyzna, w wieku ok. 25 lat, szczupły, wysoki brunet

**Stawka: 510zł** płatne po zakończeniu kontynuacji 

**Statyści kontynuacyjni 31.01 oraz 1.02 (wnętrza):**
* **MŁODY F.** - mężczyzna w wieku 30+, ciemne krótkie włosy, niewysoki
* **PROKURATOR** - mężczyzna w wieku 30+, wysoki blondyn, typ elegancki
* **FUNKCJONARIUSZ** - mężczyzna w wieku 30+

**Stawka: 340zł** płatne po drugim dniu zdjęciowym

**Statysta kontynuacyjny 31.01, 1.02, 3.02 oraz 5.02 (wnętrza):**

**WŁODEK** - mężczyzna, w wieku 40+, ok. 170cm wzrostu, otyły, z dużymi dłońmi, typ człowieka pracującego

**Stawka: 680zł** płatne po zakończeniu kontynuacji*

*UWAGA (!) możliwe dodatkowe 2 lub 3 dni zdjęciowe pod koniec lutego - wymagana dyspozycyjność. 

Zgłoszenia wysyłajcie na adres: **patrycja@podtytulem.pl**

W tytule: nazwa postaci + TC

W treści: imię i nazwisko, wiek, nr telefonu, miejscowość oraz ZDJĘCIE TWARZY I SYLWETKI tylko z dnia zgłoszenia + ZDJĘCIE DŁONI (dłonie zadbane, paznokcie naturalne!).

Zgłoszenia bez zdjęcia dłoni nie będą brane pod uwagę.

ZDJĘCIE TWARZY - portretowe selfie w dziennym świetle, na wprost, patrząc w obiektyw. Bez żadnych filtrów. Bez okularów. Bez nakrycia głowy. Kolorowe.

ZDJĘCIE SYLWETKI – aktualne, cała sylwetka

NOW ACCEPTING SUBMISSIONS IN THE GREATER LOS ANGELES AREA

SOUTHERN FRIED FUNERAL by J. Dietz Osborne and Nate Eppler

Non union theatre 

Produced by the JFed Players 
As affiliated with the Jewish Federation of the Greater San Gabriel and Pomona Valleys 

Some details:
Callbacks are in-person on Thursday February 12 in Monrovia. 

Rehearsals start February 22 in Monrovia. They will be Monday, Tuesday, Thursday nights and Sunday days, for the most part. 

Tech week begins April 25 or 26. All cast members must be fully available for tech week.

Performances will be at Ahiah Center for Spiritual Living Pasadena and will be:
Saturday, May 2 evening
Sunday, May 3 matinee 
(Wednesday, May 6 - pickup rehearsal)
Thursday, May 7 evening
Saturday, May 9 evening
Sunday, May 10 (Mother's Day) matinee
Sunday, May 10 (Mother's Day) evening show closing

Please only submit if you're available for all tech week, pickup rehearsal, and all performances.

Selected Actors will be asked to submit self tape auditions. Character breakdowns are below. 

[DOROTHY FRYE] 50s/60s female., Dewey Frye’s widow and the matriarch of the family. Strong-willed, grieving widow but also snarky and fun. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT. Lead

[SAMMY JO FRYE-LEFETTE] 30s, female. the middle child and future president of the Junior League. Maybe some anger issues, wears the pants in the marriage. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT.

[HARLENE FRYE] 30s/40s, female. the oldest child and prodigal daughter. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

[DEWEY FRYE JR] 20s, male. the youngest child and not the brightest bulb. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

[DUB FRYE] 50s/60s, male. Dorothy’s brother-in-law. Charmingly manipulative. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

[ATTICUS “ATTIE” VAN LEER] 30s/40s, male, family lawyer and on-again off-again love interest of Harlene. Intellectual. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

[BEECHAM LEFETTE] 30s, male . Sammy Jo’s husband. Slightly argumentative, doesn't appreciate being misrepresented. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

[MARTHA ANN FOX] 50s/60s, female. Dorothy‘s best friend, first name pronounced “Marthann." Rather crass and to the point, like Dorothy from Golden Girls. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

[FAIRY JUNE COOPER] 50s/60s, female. contemporary of Dorothy and Martha Ann; they’ve been friends since high school. Kind of prude and clueless, well meaning. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

[BENNY CHARLES GREENWOOD] 50s/60s male, best friend of Dewey Frye Sr. Sincere friend to the family. Not a large role, only a few scenes with some dialogue but present throughout

[OZELLA MEEKS] 60s/70s, female. chairwoman of a community committee, a position she does not take lightly. Her life's goal is organizing and planning while following rules. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

Storyline: Dewey Frye is dead and the rest of his family is left to pick up the pieces – that is if they don't kill each other first. Funerals bring out the worst, the best, and the funniest in people, and the Fryes are no exception. A big-hearted comedy about family – Southern-style.

Please submit headshots and resumes and availability to JFedProd@gmail.com 

And feel free to spread the word or share with others you think are a good fit.

items.text: The last few years I’ve taken film serious and created a Film IP Named Last of the Force. This would come with episodes and short films from the series, it has taught me a lot and pushed and challenged me. Which is a huge driving force for my personality, I’ve learned more about myself and grew close with my crew and developed a team. Thanks to you all that have assisted with this project and we have more to go before we accomplish the mission. For any filmmakers needing crew to start up your project and vision contact me. The dots always connect Last of the Force coming soon as well as more projects in the pipeline. Enjoy these films out now with a quick search on the tube.

This would come with episodes and short films from the series, it has taught me a lot and pushed and challenged me. Which is a huge driving force for my personality, I’ve learned more about myself and grew close with my crew and developed a team. Thanks to you all that have assisted with this project and we have more to go before we accomplish the mission. For any filmmakers needing crew to start up your project and vision contact me. The dots always connect Last of the Force coming soon as well as more projects in the pipeline. Enjoy these films out now with a quick search on the tube.

sharedPost.text:
علط عسري 
Lo que para nosotros son estilos musicales para los Iraquies se reduce a estilos de canto, cada estilo de canto aporta la esencia y alma de la construcción musical. Es decir, puedo tener alguno de los ritmos populares dentro de la construcción músical, pero quien le dan personalidad y por consecuencia el formato musical que posteriormente tendrá su respectivo nombre es el estilo de canto que la compone! 

Es por esto que muchas veces encontramos en canciones Iraquies ritmos populares, que para nosotr@s determinan un estilo de danza, peroooo, no siempre es así, ya que podemos podemos encontrar en ciertos estilos folclóricos como por ej, el Chobi, donde encontramos su ritmo característico propio de este estilo, y aún así encontrar algún otro ritmo popular de otros estilos. 

Te gustaría saber más sobre estilos de danza, canto, ritmos Iraquies!? 
Adentrate a este fascinante mundo en mi formación Online! 
Encontrarás distintos cursos que se adapten a tu necesidad!

🇮🇶 Formación profesional de danzas Iraquies
🇮🇶 Especialización Iraqi folk
🇮🇶 Intensivo Iraqi dance
🇮🇶 Trainning
🇮🇶 Coreografía 
🇮🇶 Talleres para escuelas 

#iraqidance #iraqifolk #marielzahraale #irak

items.text:
CASTING + CREW CALL – THIS GIRL
We're casting and building our creative team for this musical about Cynthia Lennon, the woman behind the legend. This musical is returning to Liverpool after previous sold out shows.

🎭 CASTING 🎭

Roles available:

Cynthia (Young) – Female, playing age 17–25
Prepare a monologue and a song. Must be able to follow choreography.

Cynthia (Old) – Female, playing age 40+
Prepare a monologue and a song. Must be able to follow choreography.

Stuart Sutcliffe – Male, singer/guitarist, playing age 18–25
Prepare a short monologue and a song (self-accompanied on guitar).

Aunt Mimi– Female, playing age 40+
Prepare a 2-minute monologue.

Musical Theatre Performers – 6–8 singers/dancers, any gender
Prepare a number including singing and dancing.

This is a profit share production featuring original songs including "Mother Mary" by Julian Lennon.

🎬 CREW CALL 🎬

Now seeking:
Choreographer
Lighting Technician
Stage Manager
Costume Designer
Hair & Makeup Artist

Crew roles will be paid a fixed fee, to be discussed on application. 

📍 Capstone Theatre Liverpool 
📅 Performances: 29th & 30th May 2026
🎭 Rehearsals from April at Hope Street University

Interested? Get in touch:
📧 howl.michael1963@yahoo.co.uk

Cynthia (Young) – Female, playing age 17–25
Prepare a monologue and a song. Must be able to follow choreography.

Cynthia (Old) – Female, playing age 40+
Prepare a monologue and a song. Must be able to follow choreography.

Stuart Sutcliffe – Male, singer/guitarist, playing age 18–25
Prepare a short monologue and a song (self-accompanied on guitar).

Aunt Mimi– Female, playing age 40+
Prepare a 2-minute monologue.

Musical Theatre Performers – 6–8 singers/dancers, any gender

Deadline approaching 😊 LOS ANGELES & NASHVILLE - The Satin Dollz are holding vocalist auditions in February 2026. Paid gigs. Accepting video submissions through February 1st, 2026. 

✨ LOS ANGELES & NASHVILLE — VOCALIST AUDITIONS✨

The Satin Dollz are holding vocalist auditions for our LA & Nashville divisions! 

🎤 WHAT: Female vocalists
🎶 Tight harmony trio singing (Andrews Sisters / McGuire Sisters style with soul + custom arrangements)
📍 Must be SoCal-based or Nashville-based 
🚫 Not auditioning tap dancers at this time
🌟 Paid gigs

🗓️ LA AUDITIONS:
• Video submissions due: Feb 1, 2026
• In-person auditions: Sun Feb 8 & Mon Feb 9, 2026 
• Callbacks: Wed Feb 11, 2026

🗓️ NASHVILLE AUDITIONS
• Video submissions due: Feb 1, 2026
•in-person audition dates pending 

📩 ROUND 1 – VIDEO SUBMISSION
Email a LINK (we cannot download files) to dollfaceandco@hotmail.com including:
1️⃣ Brief intro + city
2️⃣ 16 bars upbeat + 16 bars ballad (jazz preferred, no musical theatre)
3️⃣ Headshot + resume
✉️ Subject line: “First Last Name – LA Satin Dollz or Nashville Satin Dollz”

✨ Concerts • Vintage Festivals • Jazz Clubs • Corporate Events
✨ All ethnicities encouraged to submit
🔗 Full details: www.thesatindollz.com/auditions

Tag a singer who should see this 💖

#auditions #casting #vocalharmony #pinupstyle #vintagevibes

More information at www.thesatindollz.com/auditions or this FB group: https://m.facebook.com/groups/142498939757931/?ref=share&mibextid=wwXIfr

🎬 CASTING CALL – বাংলা সিনেমা 🎬
একটি নতুন বাংলা সিনেমা প্রজেক্ট–এর জন্য মহিলা শিল্পী প্রয়োজন।

👩‍🎤 কাস্টিং ডিটেইলস

🔹 বয়স ১৯–২৩ বছর → ৩ জন

🔹 বয়স ৩০–৩৫ বছর → ২ জন

📅 অডিশনের তারিখ

🗓 ৪ ফেব্রুয়ারি ২০২৬

🕛 সময়: সকাল ১২টা – দুপুর ৩টা

📍 লোকেশন

সোনারপুর কাঠ পোল,

কামধেনু মিষ্টির দোকানের পাশে

📲 যোগাযোগ (WhatsApp Only)

👉 ৯০৬২৪২৫৭৫২

📝 নোট

✔ অভিনয়ে আগ্রহী, আত্মবিশ্বাসী ও সময়ানুবর্তী প্রার্থীদের জন্য সুবর্ণ সুযোগ

✔ ফ্রেশার ও অভিজ্ঞ—উভয়েই আবেদন করতে পারবেন

items.text:
💥 Action / Thriller Actress Seeking Roles

I’m Adelola Mary Haastrup, an actress with over a decade of stage experience starting in 2011 with a gospel drama group. I have been recognized with multiple awards, including Best Minister (2012/2013), Best Dress (2013), Best Actress (2013), and 2nd Best Actress (2014). I’ve also attended acting workshops and masterclasses (2015 & 2019) to strengthen my craft.
I bring emotional depth, intensity, and versatility to any role and am now open to international projects in all genres. I am actively seeking acting opportunities that provide visa sponsorship.

📩 Contact: maryadelola_superstar@yahoo.com

items.text:
****CASTING CALL SHORT FILM****

**TITLE: PURPLE INK**

**SYNOPSIS: **The film tells the story of Chase, a teenager with undiagnosed juvenile arthritis, who makes an unlikely friendship with Daren, an old man, during his time at physical therapy.

It is a hopeful story that explores friendship, the acceptance of one's body, and aims to shed light on the disabled youth community, especially those with invisible disabilities that may go undiagnosed or untreated for many years. I grew up with the disease, which greatly limited my mobility and quality of life. Over 300k kids in the US today have some sort of rheumatoid disability, with a large number of them going undiagnosed and untreated. I hope that this film will help destigmatize and bring awareness to what youth disabilities can look like.

**Tentative Filming Dates:** August 26th-30th, 2026

Production Locations: Boston Area

Union + Non-Union. UNPAID. Actors will receive 3 on-set meals and will be compensated for travel and housing.

Project Length: 4 days 

**Please email headshot, reel, and self-tape to [colin_dowse@emerson.edu](mailto:colin_dowse@emerson.edu)

***ROLES:***

**CHASE **Male-Presenting, Any Ethnicity, 16-22 years old

Deeply introspective, Chase has juvenile arthritis and struggles with walking and pain in his lower body. He thinks this holds him back, but in reality, it makes him uncommonly observant and wise for his age. He's smart as a whip and a big classic rock fan, which helps him bond with Daren, his elderly counterpart, who helps him to accept his body for what it is and learn to love himself.

**DAREN **Male-Presenting, Any Ethnicity, 60-80 years old

A soft-spoken retired fishing captain who is admitted to physical therapy due to hip troubles. His health issues place a strain on his relationships. Meeting Chase, who struggles similarly, he develops a paternal bond with him, wishing to share his life's wisdom to help him out of his rut. In helping Chase, he learns a lot about himself.

items.text:
Hello, I’m a Dallas-based filmmaker
by the name Mopsly Man and I’m preparing my next narrative film and beginning the groundwork toward my first feature.

I have the full production gear and a clear creative direction. What I’m looking for now are committed collaborators — camera, sound, lighting, production — people who care about story, discipline, and pushing cinema forward, not just collecting credits.

This is a passion-driven project with real intention and momentum behind it. The goal is to grow together through the process and build something lasting.

If you’re serious about filmmaking and want to be part of something from the ground up, feel free to comment or reach out directly.

Below you will find a pilot short film I shot, wrote, and produced that was accepted in a Philadelphia film festival

https://youtu.be/jLY9aTxLb-A?si=xyTyqYGTL8-oXEqx

Fundacja Performatywy we współpracy z CBK Fama zapraszają na kolejną edycję WORK IN PROGRESS — wydarzenia skierowanego do osób działających w obszarze sztuk performatywnych. ✨
To wyjątkowa okazja, by zaprezentować i przetestować swoje aktualne projekty sceniczne (cyrkowe, taneczne, teatralne i inne), które są jeszcze w trakcie powstawania i nie miały dotąd swojej oficjalnej premiery. 💃

W ramach wydarzenia uczestnicy(-czki) otrzymają wsparcie specjalistów(-ek) z różnych dziedzin artystycznych, którzy pomogą w dalszym rozwoju projektów. 👏 To także moment na refleksję i sprawdzenie, czy obrany kierunek twórczy jest tym właściwym. 

📅 Zgłoszenia będą przyjmowane poprzez formularz zgłoszeniowy od 08.02.

👉 WORK IN PROGRESS to również wydarzenie otwarte dla publiczności. Jego celem jest zwrócenie uwagi na proces twórczy, często niewidoczny dla widzów, a stanowiący ogromną część artystycznej pracy. Zapraszamy wszystkich, którzy chcą zajrzeć za kulisy powstawania etiud scenicznych lub po prostu zobaczyć występy uczestników(-czek) na scenie. 

Wstęp na wydarzenie będzie biletowany. Szczegóły dotyczące biletów już wkrótce. 🎟️
_________________________

💎 Gdzie?
CBK Fama
ul. Bolesława Krzywoustego 286
Wrocław / Psie Pole

💎 Kiedy?
14.03.25r. (sobota)
start: 17:00 
⚠️ Godzina wydarzenia może ulec zmianie. 

💎 Pytania?
Napisz do nas na: performatywy@gmail.com

💡 INFORMACJE NA TEMAT WSTĘPU I HARMONOGRAMU JUŻ WKRÓTCE! 
_________________________

Organizowane przez Fundację Performatywy i CBK Fama wydarzenie ma na celu wspieranie rozwoju środowiska performatywnego we Wrocławiu i poza jego granicami.

Zapraszamy także na edycję dla młodzieży (14-18), która odbywa się 15.03.2025r.: https://www.facebook.com/events/866953182844584

**Szukam modelki na zasadzie TFP Gliwice/Katowice ( Śląsk )**

 

Szukam pań które nie krępują się własnego ciała i chciałaby mieć ciekawą pamiątkę w postaci klimatycznych zdjęć. Wiem jak bardzo jest ważna akceptacja własnego ciała bo przez to też możemy inaczej funkcjonować. Przez takie zdjęcia można również tego dokonać. Sesja w głównej mierze jest jako taki motywator.

 

Poszukuje kobiety w **wieku od 25 **lat nie koniecznie z doświadczeniem pozowania, na zasadach Tfp mieszkającej w Gliwicach lub okolicach Zabrze czy Katowice najdalej. Posiadam na wyposażeniu mini studio z kilkoma tłami oraz lampami. Mam również duży wybór kostiumów i gadżetów do wykorzystywania. Główny motyw do kobieta: Piękna i drapieżna! Sama sesja trwa przeważnie od 1,5h do 2h w zalezności od motywów.

** **

**Temat 1 – ‘’Kobieta mafii 1930’’**

Postać kobiety osadzona w 1930 roku w roli bogatej kobiety, która trudni się gangsterstwem. Przewidziane są ujęcia m.in. przy stoliku na którym są pieniądze, wino, rewolwer. Tło jest wydrukowane w formie muru, cegieł. Motyw sensualny.

** **

**Temat 2 – ‘’Wampirzyca w baroku 1700’’**

Postać kobiety ubrana najpierw w suknie czarną oraz peleryne z kapturem. Do tego czarna długa peruka oraz czarne paznokcie. W kolejnym etapie sesji motyw sensualny.

** **

**Temat 3 – ‘’Duchy lasu’’**

Postać kobiety ubrana w wianek i w pelerynę z otwartym przodem. W dłoni ma zakrwawiony sierp. Usta czarne oraz paznokcie.

** **

**Temat 4 – ‘’Kleopatra’’**

Postać kobiety z czarna peruką w stylu Kleopatry. W prawej recę trzymac będzie berło Anubisa a w drugiej ręcę księgę umarłych. Na biodrach będzie mieć jedynie klasyczne odzienie z 2 części. Na klatce piersiowej założony będzie napierśnik złoty.

** **

**Temat 5 – ‘’Odważna Piratka ‘’**

Postać kobiety ubrana w strój piracki: kamizelka, koszula, kapelusz, spodnie i kapelusz a do tego rekwizyty pistolet czy kufel piwa.

 

**Temat 6 – ‘’Lara Croft ‘’**

Postać kobiety wzorowanej z tytułowej gry Tomb Rider Lary Croft.  Kobiete będzie przebywać w swojej bazie i badać nowe znaleziska pod lupą.

 

** **

**Zapraszam na stronę**

** **

**Facebook Łukasz Magiera – Fotografia**

www.instagram.com/lukasz.magiera.official

Więcej informacji na Priv

items.text:
# **CASTING CALL **

Hi,

I am Pragati Gupta, seeking actors for short scenes to be filmed for a graduate film directing class at UNCW.

Here is the breakdown for the “Sorry We Missed You” scene recreation.

*Scene brief:* When a working-class father discovers his teenage son’s quiet rebellion, the family is forced to confront the cost of survival versus the promise of a better future.

**SEB**: 15-18 yrs old, (Male, Teenage son, Actors 18+ who can convincingly play younger are welcome.)

**ABBIE**: 40-50 yrs old, (Female, Mother, Calm authority, controlled intensity)

Actors will need to be available on **Wednesday, Feb 11, from 8:30am-12pm**. The shoot location will be on the UNCW Campus.

Submit the following (headshot, acting resume, video audition) to pg7528@uncw.edu.

Subject line: “Character Name” in “Sorry We Missed You”.

Please include-

Name:

Age:

Recent photo:

Acting resume:

Submissions must be received by the morning of **Feb 4, 2026**.

🎬 **CAST & CREW CALL – INDEPENDENT THRILLER FILM (1-DAY SHOOT)**
📍 Forney, Texas | One Location | Psychological Thriller

Hi everyone —
I’m producing and directing a contained psychological thriller titled *Unraveled Vows*, and I’m looking to collaborate with passionate actors and crew members who want to be part of something cinematic, intimate, and festival-ready.

This is a low-budget, high-quality indie film designed to be shot in one day, one house, with only 3 main characters — very performance-driven and story-focused.

The finished film will be pitched to executives, producers, and streaming platforms, and everyone involved will receive ownership/percentage participation in the project, not just a credit.

If you want to help build something meaningful instead of just another gig, this is for you.

🎭 **CASTING (3 Principal Roles)**

**James (Male, 30–40)**
Charismatic, calm, rising politician. Loving husband with a darker, calculated side.

**Fatima (Female, late 20s–early 30s)**
Emotionally layered, vulnerable but strong. Carries guilt and secrets. Lead role.

**Ken (Male, 30–40)**
Charming but dangerous. Quiet, psychological menace. Intense presence.

(Strong acting ability required – dialogue-heavy roles)

🎥 **CREW NEEDED**

• Camera Operator / DP
• Sound Recordist / Boom Mic Owner
• Editor
• Sound Design / Post Audio
• PA (optional)

If you own gear (camera, boom, audio equipment), huge plus.

🤝 **What You Get**

• Ownership/percentage participation in the film
• IMDb credit
• Festival + streaming exposure
• Transportation stipend
• Food provided
• 1-day shoot only
• Collaborative, creative environment

This is perfect for actors and filmmakers building reels, credits, and real projects.

items.text:
**CASTING CALL FOR WEB SERIES**

Hi everyone! I’m seeking actors for the first episode in a comedy web series, *Vancouver I Think We Should See Other Cities*. It revolves around a young man navigating the surreal everyday life of the Canadian city.

This first episode titled “Turn Down The Heat” is surreal but also risqué in what I hope is the best way possible. It’s important to note that nothing of graphic nature is ever depicted onscreen. 

My number one priority is ensuring a welcome and safe environment where we are able to collaborate on a strong project. If you have any questions regarding the material before submitting, please DM me and I am more than happy to discuss. 

**Logline:**

A young man, Paul, goes to a meeting of the Hudson Williams Fan Club only to realize that he may be out of his depth.

**Production Details:**
* Location: Vancouver, BC
* Filming Dates: Latter half of February 2026 (TBD)
* Non-Union / Volunteer
* Food and IMDb credit provided

**ROLES**

**STEVEN - Male, Mid-Late 20s (Open Ethnicity)**

The charismatic leader of the Hudson Williams Fan Club.

**JULIA - Female, Mid-Late 20s (Open Ethnicity)**

A member of the Hudson Williams Fan Club. She is understanding and supportive to Paul when he needs it.

**HUDSON WILLIAMS FAN CLUB MEMBERS - Mid-Late 20s (Open Ethnicity)**

The rest of the group, unfazed by the events of the meeting. 

**TO APPLY**

Please send the following to [vaithinkweshouldseeothercities@gmail.com](mailto:vaithinkweshouldseeothercities@gmail.com)

Subject: “EPISODE #1 - [CHARACTER NAME]”
* Headshot
* Resume
* Demo reel (if possible)
* Availability (Latter half of February 2026)

Thank you so much for your time. Take care and have a great day.

items.text:
Model | Performer | Wellness Professional
With over 80+ professional photoshoots under my belt — including paid projects across fashion, lifestyle, artistic, body paint, and life modeling — I have developed a versatile presence in front of the camera backed by a disciplined lifestyle and unique skillset. 

Height    195 cm  | 6.5
Weight  85kg | 187 pounds
Neck      40 cm  | 15.7 |
Chest    102 cm  | 40.2 |
Waist     78 cm  | 30.7 |
Hips.  96 cm |  37 |
Sleeve   81 | cm  | 31.9 |
Inseam   81 | cm  | 31.9 |
Shoe Size  45  EU   | 10.5 UK
Skin Tone: Medium-light  
Eye Color: Brown 
Hair color: Dark brown 

Alongside modeling, I bring on-screen experience from multiple TV shows, interview formats, podcasts, and extra appearances in my home country, while continuously expanding into acting and performance-based work. 

Performance Skills
• Aerial Acrobatics — Hoop, Trapeze, Silks, Rope (Beginner–Intermediate)
• Contact staff — Intermediate
• Staff spinning - Intermediate 
• Katana/Aikido - Intermediate 
• Yoga — Advanced
• Swimming — Advanced
• Parkour - Intermediate+
• Dance - freestyle freedom of expression intuitive improvised movement 
Some stage combat, shooting, falling experience 

Professional Background
• Qualified Swimming Coach, Yoga Teacher, and Personal Trainer with 14+ years of teaching experience.
• Deep expertise in health, movement, breath, wellness, and high performance. 

What Sets Me Apart
• Strong work ethic, relentless discipline, and ability to perform under discomfort, pressure, and challenging conditions.

**Szukam modelki na zasadzie TFP Gliwice/Katowice ( Śląsk ) +40 – bez doświadczenia**

 

Szukam pań które nie krępują się własnego ciała i chciałaby mieć ciekawą pamiątkę w postaci klimatycznych zdjęć. Wiem jak bardzo jest ważna akceptacja własnego ciała bo przez to też możemy inaczej funkcjonować. Przez takie zdjęcia można również tego dokonać. Sesja w głównej mierze jest jako taki motywator. Tematem sesji będzie sensualny Anioł.

 

Poszukuje kobiety w **wieku od + 40  **lat nie koniecznie z doświadczeniem pozowania, na zasadach Tfp mieszkającej w Gliwicach lub okolicach Zabrze czy Katowice najdalej. Posiadam na wyposażeniu mini studio z kilkoma tłami oraz lampami. Mam również duży wybór kostiumów i gadżetów do wykorzystywania. Główny motyw do kobieta: Piękna i drapieżna! Sama sesja trwa przeważnie od 1,5h do 2h w zalezności od motywów.

** **

**Zapraszam na stronę**

** **

sharedPost.text:
Call for Entries to the CITTADOR INTERNATIONAL FILM FESTIVAL!

We’re approaching our first deadline of the season, and we’re officially calling on filmmakers from around the world to submit their work to the Cittador International Film Festival (CIFF)!

This year is extra special: Cittador IFF celebrates its 5th anniversary - our first milestone — and we would love to celebrate it together with you and your films.

Cittador IFF is dedicated to showcasing and awarding outstanding independent cinema based solely on artistic quality. Free from commercial constraints, we celebrate films that are bold, original, imaginative, and inspiring - stories that live beyond the mainstream, regardless of genre, background, age, or filmmaking experience.
Our international jury carefully evaluates every submission. Selected and award-winning films receive a public jury statement, highlighting what makes each work unique and meaningful. Award-winning films will be screened in front of an international audience in the famous CineCenter Cinema in Vienna.

We also empower filmmakers to share their voices: selected filmmakers can submit a written interview to be published in the official festival catalog — whether award-winning or not.

Submit now via Filmfreeway, Festhome or TouJiang.

Be part of our journey. Be part of our anniversary.
Submit your film and celebrate independent cinema with CIFF!

https://cittador-iff.com

 #cittadorinternationalfilmfestival #callforentries #filmfestival #cittadoriff

message.text:
Are you an independent filmmaker ready to showcase your work on an international stage? The Cittador International Film Festival (CIFF) in Vienna celebrates inspiration, creativity, and uniqueness in cinema.

Our video “CITTADOR, my CITTADOR! – Winged Words” captures the festival’s spirit and philosophy – highlighting what makes CIFF stand out as a platform for true artistic expression.

Based on the book CITTADOR, my CITTADOR! – Winged Words by Ana Bilic, this video reflects the core values that guide the festival’s film selection: artistic vision, originality, and emotional impact.

Submit your film today and join a global community of storytellers who think differently.

🔗 Learn more & apply: https://iff.cittador.com

#cittadorfilmfestival #indiefilmfest #independentfilm #ciffvienna

items.text:
Dieses Retreat ist kein Urlaub und kein klassisches Coaching.

Es ist ein Raum, in dem du als Schauspieler:in an deiner Wirkung arbeitest –
fernab von Alltag, Ablenkung und Konkurrenzdenken.

Fünf Tage auf Fuerteventura bedeuten Fokus.
Auf dich.
Auf das, was dich vor der Kamera greifbar, interessant und buchbar macht.

Hier geht es nicht um Technik oder „richtig spielen“.
Sondern darum, als Persönlichkeit klarer zu werden,
Präsenz aufzubauen
und dich nicht länger anzupassen, um zu gefallen.

In einer Gruppe von Gleichgesinnten entsteht ein Raum,
in dem du dich zeigen kannst – ohne Maske, ohne Druck.
Genau dort beginnt die Veränderung, die auch im Casting spürbar wird.

🎬 Wenn du mehr erfahren möchtest,
kommentiere „Retreat“
und erhalte den Link zum Essenz-Infocall
🗓 08. Februar | 11:00 Uhr

**Fine Then, I'll Do It On My Own **

An intensive 2-day practical workshop focusing on making solo work led by award-winning writer and performer Rachel Mars.

Whether you are making your first/second/seventh solo work, get ready to read, write, devise and share material in a playful and supportive space.

 

🗓️23rd-24th February 2026

📍Hackney Showroom, Finsbury Park

⭐️ Free bursary place available

items.text:
CASTING - BLOOD & PAPER

Genre: Drama, Coming of Age

Synopsis: After a violent altercation leaves her suspended from school, anger-prone Demi becomes obsessed with obtaining her Tribal ID to prove that she belongs somewhere. But as her need to protect others pushes them farther away, she must confront the realization that identity is not something you can find on a piece of paper.

Roles:

DEMI: (Late teens/early 20’s, Female, Black/African Descent, Racially Ambiguous, Lead)

A high schooler with anger issues, a lack of friends, but a fierce loyalty to protect those around her. None of her emotions come with a middle ground: when she’s sad, she’s inconsolable, when she’s angry, she’s furious. Ends up pushing people away due to this nature. Begins an obsessive attempt to obtain her Tribal ID in hopes that it will make her feel like she belongs somewhere.

LENA: (Late teens/early 20’s, Female, Any Ethnicity, Supporting)

Demi’s Older Sister. Loves and cares for Demi, but secretly holds some resentment towards the problem child that is her sister. She is moving across the country for college, and is worried how Demi will do without her there.

ADRIAN: (Late teens/early 20’s, Male, Native American/Indigenous Descent, Hispanic/Latino, Supporting)

An attractive, native farm hand, and childhood best friend of Demi. He admires her protective nature, and has always had a crush on her .. though Demi has always been too oblivious to notice.

DRUNKARDS: (20-30, Male, Any Ethnicity)

Two drunk men on the street who catcall Lena, not realizing that doing so will incur the wrath of Demi. 

Production Company: Nymesis Studios, Dir. Corinne Nuncio

Production Type: Student Film

Contact Information: Corinne@nymesisstudios.com, please reach out with headshot and resume for sides. (If you don’t have a headshot or resume, please reach out for sides regardless)

Use BLOOD & PAPER - ROLE in your email header.

Run Time: Short

Compensation: Unpaid. Footage provided, final copy of film provided, meals provided.

Union Status: Non-Union

Audition Information: Virtual, Self Tape auditions due by Saturday, February 7th. Submit to Corinne@nymesisstudios.com. In-person callback date, early-mid February.

Shooting Schedule: Shoots 6-7 days, March 8-14. Planned rehearsal dates in late February, early March.

Filming Location: Sedalia, Denver, Aurora

Project Description: We will be shooting on a ranch around real animals (specifically horses and cows), please be aware for any possible allergies.

topComments.text: Right on! A Native American story line. I wish I fit the script.

items.text:
My Spring monologue is a scene excerpt from the TV series, "IT: Welcome to Derry" (Episode 5, "29 Niebolt Street") in the role of Dick Hallorann, performed by actor Chris Chalk.

After a few subtle revisions to make it mine, I separated this 60-second monologue into 3 parts to work on my actions and objectives for each piece.

At least 5 actors have portrayed Dick Hallorann across film, television, and stage adaptations of Stephen King's universe. The actors include Scatman Crothers (1980), Melvin Van Peebles (1997), Arthur Woodley (2016 opera), Carl Lumbly (2019), and Chris Chalk (2025).

With over 80+ professional photoshoots under my belt — including paid projects across fashion, lifestyle, artistic, body paint, and life modeling — I have developed a versatile presence in front of the camera backed by a disciplined lifestyle and unique skillset.

Skin Tone: Medium-light  

Eye Color: Brown 

Hair color: Dark brown 

Alongside modeling, I bring on-screen experience from multiple TV shows, interview formats, podcasts, and extra appearances in my home country, while continuously expanding into acting and performance-based work. 

Performance Skills

• Aerial Acrobatics — Hoop, Trapeze, Silks, Rope (Beginner–Intermediate)

• Contact staff — Intermediate

• Staff spinning - Intermediate 

• Katana/Aikido - Intermediate 

• Yoga — Advanced

• Swimming — Advanced

• Parkour - Intermediate+

• Dance - freestyle freedom of expression intuitive improvised movement 

Some stage combat, shooting, falling experience 

Professional Background

• Qualified Swimming Coach, Yoga Teacher, and Personal Trainer with 14+ years of teaching experience.

• Deep expertise in health, movement, breath, wellness, and high performance. 

What Sets Me Apart

• Strong work ethic, relentless discipline, and ability to perform under discomfort, pressure, and challenging conditions.

• Holistic approach to self-regulation — always camera-ready, physically prepared, mentally sharp, and adaptable.

• Highly motivated in building my craft and presence — I create, edit, and post content daily across YouTube, TikTok, and Instagram to develop audience. 

Seeking opportunities in modeling, acting, and performance — primarily in the UK, but open to international projects.

22

items.text:
Jeg voksede op i Calumet County, Wisconsin, så jeg kan fortælle dig, at denne opskrift er den ægte vare! Vi tog til Schwarz's Supper Club efter messen hver søndag, før børnene blev født. Det var stedet at være, så man ventede i evigheder på sin mad. Ostepålæg og en relish-bakke var altid meget nødvendige for at holde en overnatning! Jeg har savnet vores supperklubber meget, siden jeg flyttede sydpå, så jeg er begyndt at lave en lignende menu, når veninder kommer på besøg. De velkendte smagsoplevelser er et lille stykke af hjemmet "

I am currently Producing a brand new show for Channel 4 in creating an alternative court to resolve your disputes, without the usual costs and delays.

Has a dispute got out of hand?

Do you want to draw a line under a conflict that’s been going on too long?

In this brand-new series, from the makers of *Long Lost Family,* we’ll open the doors of a fast-track court that will help people settle their civil disputes.

All those who take part will be provided with **free expert legal representation**.

**We are looking for people who would like to sort out a dispute in a swift and legally-binding hearing.**

Why should you take part?
* Do you feel that you are owed money, an apology, or simply justice on a matter?
Perhaps you want a refund on a service you paid for? Maybe you feel an ex-partner or family member has taken more than their fair share? Whatever the issue, big or small, this could be your chance to have your story heard and to reach a final verdict.
* Perhaps the civil court system feels too complex, too costly, or just takes too long.
* Perhaps you’d like the free advice of some of Britain’s top lawyers (likely in region of £10,000)

**If you want to apply or have a no obligation conversation with someone to find out more then drop me a message**

**CASTING CALL** – LONDON – STUDENT SHORT FILM: "MUSE"

Project: MUSE. Genre: Psychological Drama / Indie. Status: Unpaid (Full travel reimbursement, catering, and HD colour-graded footage for your reel provided).

THE STORY: *MUSE* is an atmospheric study of aesthetic obsession and psychological erasure. We follow Miles, a young man who is slowly "edited" and physically reshaped by his partner, Eliza, until he is no longer a person, but a project.
ROLES:

MILES (Lead): Male, 18-25, Vulnerable and soft-featured. Miles is the emotional spine of the film.
* Note: This role requires a strong vocal performance for an intimate voice-over and a willingness to undergo a stylistic physical transformation (wardrobe/styling) on camera.

ELIZA (Lead): Female, 18-25 Magnetic, clinical, and detached. She views the world—and her partner—through a lens of artistic perfection.
* Note: Looking for an actor who can command the screen with minimal movement and a "heavy" presence.

LIAM (Supporting): Male, 20-30. Charming, easy-going, and a "lad's lad". He represents the "normal" world that Eliza has rejected.
* Note: A pivotal dialogue scene that requires natural, socially fluent energy.
DETAILS:
* Location: London
* Dates: TBD (Late February – Early March)
* Writer/Producer: Emma Sidwell

TO APPLY: Please email emmasidwell@icloud.com with the role you are applying for.

sharedPost.text:
Liebe Produktionen, Produzenten aber auch liebe Agenturen und Filmschaffende in Deutschland:

+++ Der  erste Gagenkatalog für Kompars*innen und Kleindarsteller*innen ist seit ein paar Tagen öffentlich! +++

Die darin angegebenen Beträge sind Empfehlungen der Initiative Faire Gagen und beruhen auf den Erfahrungen vieler etablierter Filmschaffender und ihren Rückmeldungen an unsere Initiative, als auch auf Gespräche unsererseits mit Agenturen und Produktionen. 
 
Dabei werden auch schrittweise gewählte Ziele des Katalogs (z.B. von budget-schwächeren Produktionen) zu mehr Fairness und damit auch wieder zu höherer Motivation der Filmschaffenden führen.

Nachweislich kommt es gerade durch etablierte Filmschaffende zu weniger Problemen beim Buchungsprocedere und ganz besonders am Set, als bei ständig neu gecasteten Menschen, die eben oft ganz andere Beweggründe haben, wie z.B. "einfach mal dabei sein" und dies auch selbst für eigentlich nicht mehr Faire Gagen. 

Dazu jedoch nur als Beispiel, die bekanntlich  immer höher steigende Zahl von kurzfristigen Buchungs-Absagen und dabei besonders das Nichterscheinen am Drehort ohne Absage, festgebuchter Kompars*innen. 
Besonders letzteres sehen selbstverständlich auch wir als ein absolutes "No Go" gegenüber unseren Produktionen und Agenturen an.

+++ Eine faire Bezahlung aber auch das schrittweise Umdenken bezüglich veralteter Setregeln, oder kaum noch nachvollziebarer Buchungsbeschränkungen (Beispiel Altersgrenzen) wird, verbunden mit  einer höheren Wertschätzung gegenüber den Filmschaffenden,  nicht nur zu  einem besseren Arbeitsklima führen, sondern zwangsläufig auch ein Garant für direkte  Zeit- und Kosteneinsparungen der Produktionen sein. +++

Auch die Agenturen könnten so zumindest bei dem für jede Produktion so wichtigen Faktor "Zeit" profitieren und so noch effizienter und professioneller für ihre zu betreuenden Produktionen arbeiten.
Tatsächlich werden nur so beide Seiten mittel- und langfristig provitieren. 
Der leider oft voreilig eingesetzte  Rotstift mancher Produktionen hat bereits viele etablierte und zuverlässige Filmschaffende in den letzten  Jahren zwangsläufig verprellt. 

Daher sehen wir auch ganz allgemein, dass eine Philosophie von "Einsparungen" und "Weiter so" (auf einem sich nicht mehr lohnenden Gagen-Niveau) dem deutschen Film eher schaden als nützen wird.
Produktionen, die sich eh schon an faire Gagen und Zuschläge halten sind hier natürlich weniger angesprochen. Sie dienen für uns jedoch als absolut beispielhaft für alle anderen, denn sie zeigen uns schon seit vielen Jahren sehr eindrucksvoll, dass Fairness und Wertschätzung eben doch ganz einfach funktioniert.

Initiative Faire Gagen.

film fabularny lata 70te

* **PRACOWNICY ADMINISTRACJI** (11 lutego)- panowie ok. 25 - 50 lat. **Stawka 200 zł** ( 1 dzień zdjęciowy + charakteryzacja)

**Wytyczne charakteryzacji:**

**MĘŻCZYŹNI:**

- WŁOSY- raczej dłuższe, nachodzące na uszy i kark. Nieakceptowane są włosy obcięte bardzo krótko maszynką ,wygolone boki i kark z dłuższą górą, wycięte wzorki na włosach oraz nienaturalne kolory oraz farbowane np. na czarny.

- ZAROST - mogą być wąsy ,baki, lub pełny zarost ale naturalny niestylizowany u barbera.

- panowie na mundurowych mogą mieć włosy krótsze, odsłonięte uszy i kark, ale niewygoleni maszynką. Ogoleni na gładko.

Zgłoszenia poproszę na adres: **[jarek.drzycimski@podtytulem.pl](mailto:jarek.drzycimski@podtytulem.pl)**

W treści: imię i nazwisko, wiek, nr telefonu, miejscowość + wymiary: wzrost, klatka, pas, biodra, rozmiar ubrania i buta

ZDJĘCIE TWARZY - portretowe selfie w dziennym świetle, na wprost, patrząc w obiektyw. Bez żadnych filtrów. Bez okularów. Bez nakrycia głowy. Kolorowe.

sharedPost.text:
🎙️ CASTING do projektu niekomercyjnego: szukamy 6 nowych prowadzących do Klubu Qltura (YouTube)
Chcesz spróbować swoich sił w podcaście, rozwinąć talent dziennikarski, uczyć się prowadzenia rozmów i budować własną opinię? To może być Twoja szansa.

📺 Kanał: https://youtube.com/@klubqltura?si=P3DMt1qYE9RWDGgf

Kogo szukamy?

Szukamy 6 osób w każdym wieku - zależy nam na międzypokoleniowym wydźwięku i zderzeniu różnych perspektyw. Będziemy mieszać składy prowadzących.

Ważne informacje:

📍 Warszawa, 
📅 13 lutego 2026 
🕘 Casting odbywać się będzie w godz. 9:00–17:00 (dokładny adres i godzina Twojego wejścia dostaniesz po wstępnej selekcji)
🎥 Nagrania: maks. 2 razy w miesiącu
✅ Udział jest darmowy - na ten moment nie jest to płatna współpraca (nie wypłacamy wynagrodzenia).

Jak się zgłosić?

Wyślij maila na adres 
📧 kontakt@pcpir.pl 
ze zgłoszeniem zawierającym:

1️⃣Krótko o Tobie (w jednej wiadomości):
 • imię i nazwisko
 • wiek i miasto
 • telefon + e-mail
 • linki do social mediów

2️⃣Twoje mocne tematy (wypisz 3–6):
np. film/seriale, muzyka, popkultura, społeczeństwo, psychologia w codzienności, relacje, media i internet, trendy, polityka, sport/kibicowanie, technologia/AI, praca/pieniądze.

3️⃣ Demo video (max 2 min):
plik albo link. W demo: przedstaw się i opowiedz krótko 1 temat tak, jakbyś prowadził/a fragment odcinka.

🧩 Wskazówka do demo: najlepiej, jeśli w 2 min pokażesz: flow, energię, myśl i pointę.

Creative Croatian language workshop for adults with basic knowledge of language. We will meet once a week and learn Croatian trough supportive and funny ways talking about everyday issues. 

Workshops begin on Saturday 7th of February 2026. We will meet every Saturday at 11.00 to 12.30 in KNAP classroom, Ivanićgradska 41 a. We will skip 21st Feb and Saturday holidays when KNAP is closed.

CASTING CALL – JAPANESE HOSTS
Non-Union | Location: DTLA

Rehearsal: Sat 2/21

Shoot Dates: Sun 2/22 & Mon 2/23

Seeking vibrant, dynamic, camera-friendly Japanese-speaking hosts for an on-camera pop-up experience featuring the latest Japanese tech devices. Talent must be fluent in Japanese (bilingual preferred), energetic, welcoming, and comfortable interacting with real guests on camera. Strong improv skills and live-event energy are a plus.

ROLES:

• Hiro – Male, 20–40, Asian | Principal | $500/12

• Sakura – Female, 20–40, East Asian | Principal | $450/12

REQUIREMENTS:

Hosts will guide guests through a hands-on tech experience, demonstrating and showcasing new Japanese devices in a fun, engaging way. Must be confident speaking on camera, engaging the public, and adapting naturally in a live, filmed environment.

SUBMIT:

• Headshot

• Resume

• Reel (if available)

• Social media handles

• 30–60 second audition video introducing yourself and welcoming guests to try the latest Japanese tech devices.

Please demonstrate how you would guide and excite guests, and mix in Japanese language naturally (greetings, explanations, reactions, or commentary).

Send submissions to:

📧 liferunner01@gmail.com

Include your name, email, and contact information.

items.text:
Strike a Pose: A Fashion Fairytale
Film Auditions 

It is a non paid film

Overview: Elssya Morgan wants more than anything to be a fashion designer. But her aunt Heather and cousins won’t let that happen. But when millionaires, the Windors, throw a party for their son and invite all the top designers in Michigan to the party. Elyssa takes her chance to show her talent to everyone and maybe steal the heart of Jake Windsor. 

If you’re interested in auditioning, please send your headshot, resume, and reel to cecem143@gmail.com. Once you send your information over, you will receive sides to do a self-tape. We will accept them until February 15th, 2026, at 11:59 pm. (if you’re auditioning for Jake, and you get an email back after your self-tape, you will be asked to do a chemistry test with the lead actress.)Filming locations are Birmingham, Royal Oak, and the Metro Detroit Area. Looking forward to hearing from you all. 

Jake Windsor - African American, dark hair, mid 20s, charming, handsome, well-dressed, tall, smart, he has dreams for his future, and he hates being controlled by his parents.

Heather Morgan - White, in her mid-30s, Elyssa’s aunt, wicked, wears fancy clothes, mean, rude, selfish, tries to make herself look young for her age, has two daughters, Giselle and Clarissa.

Giselle Morgan - White, in her mid-20s, Elyssa's cousin, spoiled brat, mean, demanding, nasty, wears too much makeup, dresses fashionably, acts like she’s better than everyone else, 

Clarissa Morgan - White, in her mid 20s, Elyssa's cousin, mean, thinks of herself as a spoiled brat, rude, bossy, dresses fashionably, acts like she’s better than everyone else, wears too much makeup.

Ryan Chanel- White, in his mid 20s, flamboyant, positive, energetic, charismatic, witty, introspective, and fashionable, Elyssa's best friend.

Henry Levell- African American, in his mid 30s, posh, elegant, witty, mildly sarcastic, he is Jake’s family butler and always tries to have Jake’s back.

Ruby Windsor - African American, she’s in her mid 30s to early 40s, Jake’s mom,  snobby, elegant, sophisticated, pushy, noisy, sometimes funny, controlling, acts like a know-it-all, dresses well.

items.summary:
Strike a Pose: A Fashion Fairytale
Film Auditions 

It is a non paid film

Overview: Elssya Morgan wants more than anything to be a fashion designer. But her aunt Heather and cousins won’t let that happen. But when millionaires, the Windors, throw a party for their son and invite all the top designers in Michigan to the party. Elyssa takes her chance to show her talent to everyone and maybe steal the heart of Jake Windsor. 

If you’re interested in auditioning, please send your headshot, resume, and reel to cecem143@gmail.com. Once you send your information over, you will receive sides to do a self-tape. We will accept them until February 15th, 2026, at 11:59 pm. (if you’re auditioning for Jake, and you get an email back after your self-tape, you will be asked to do a chemistry test with the lead actress.)Filming locations are Birmingham, Royal Oak, and the Metro Detroit Area. Looking forward to hearing from you all. 

Jake Windsor - African American, dark hair, mid 20s, charming, handsome, well-dressed, tall, smart, he has dreams for his future, and he hates being controlled by his parents.

Heather Morgan - White, in her mid-30s, Elyssa’s aunt, wicked, wears fancy clothes, mean, rude, selfish, tries to make herself look young for her age, has two daughters, Giselle and Clarissa.

Giselle Morgan - White, in her mid-20s, Elyssa's cousin, spoiled brat, mean, demanding, nasty, wears too much makeup, dresses fashionably, acts like she’s better than everyone else,

Hello, dear artists. We are looking for dancers (solo), dance couples
For the show project "BeFree" in Turkey (Antalya) for the 2026 season.

Work in 5⭐️ hotels, one show a day, 2 fixed days off per month.

NO CONSUMPTION/NO ANIMATION

The employer provides comfortable accommodation for artists and 4 meals 🥘 per day, a work visa and medical insurance.

The salary starts at $850

To participate, please send your resume, preferably a video where you dance yourself, a video of your training and some photos to jiddanceproject@gmail.com

Telegram - @jackinyo

Whatsup - +995591057166

DETAILED INFORMATION AND CONDITIONS WILL BE PROVIDED AFTER YOU SEND YOUR RESUME. Thank you.

items.text:
Only one space left for our upcoming Demidov Two Day Intensive running May 23rd & 24th at Pushkin House in London! 

This Two Day Intensive will introduce actors to Demidov’s unique approach to accessing our inner freedom, cultivating our intuition, perception, spontaneity, and ability to surrender fully to our inner urges and the truth of our experience in the moment. 

Over the course of this weekend, we will discover how to orient ourselves in the circumstances of a given text and to surrender to them fully. We will learn how circumstances become 'given', and how they become clearer and deeper every time we repeat a scene. We will learn to let ourselves be driven by the force of circumstances, rather than forcing ourselves to do, think or feel anything. In this way, living as character becomes effortless and spontaneous.

This Intensive is for actors both new to the Demidov work, and also for those who would like to go deeper into it. 

The Demidov Organic Acting Technique empowers actors to connect deeply with their unique creative individuality by guiding them to recognise and trust their innate artistic instincts. It is an approach that cultivates faith in the actors’ own talent and foster spontaneous performances that emerge organically, allowing actors to consistently access inspiration and fully express their true creative potential. 

Click the link below to read more and email us at [office@demidovstudiolondon.com](mailto:office@demidovstudiolondon.com) with any questions!

https://www.demidovstudiolondon.com/courses/demidov-two-day-intensive-may26

~

Demidov Studio London

The UK’s only certified Demidov Acting School

Located at Pushkin House, 5a Bloomsbury Square, London WC1A 2TA

[demidovstudiolondon.com](http://demidovstudiolondon.com/)

All classes and courses taught by studio Founder & Director @andrei_biziorek 

@pushkinhouselondon

items.text:
*** CASTING CALL FOR STUDENT SHORT - UNPAID (OTHER BENEFITS) - See below ***

Hi everyone,

I’m currently casting for an 8-10 minute student short film ‘**ONEIROPHOBIA**’, a psychological drama that explores trauma, guilt, and the fear of dreaming. The story follows a young man, Liam, who is haunted by recurring nightmares connected to the death of his younger brother, until a therapist/oneirologist begins to help him unravel these dark visions. The film delves into themes of family conflict, grief, mental health, and trauma.

We’re looking to cast 4 characters:
1. **LIAM DAY **(Male | Playing Age: 18-24 | Any Ethnicity | Lead Role)
2. **ROBERT/ROBYN (‘ROB’) WALKER **(Any Gender | Playing Age: 40-50 | Any Ethnicity | Supporting Role)
3. **LESLIE DAY **(Female | Voice Over | Any Ethnicity | Supporting Role)
4. **THE RUNNER **(Male | Playing Age: 20-30 | Any Ethnicity | Supporting Role)

**Shoot Details:**
The film will be shot over five days but the different roles will be required on different days. Liam is the only role that would be required on all days. All filming will take place in and around Glasgow and is scheduled for weekdays between 16th-24th March 2026 (exact dates TBC).

**Pay and compensation:**
Please note that this is a **no-budget student short film**. While we’re unable to offer payment, we’re committed to ensuring that all actors gain meaningful value from this opportunity. All cast members will receive f**ootage from the final edit for use in their showreels** (and we’re happy to assist with cutting this if needed). We’re also currently working to arrange **complimentary headshots** and high-quality **BTS pics** for successful applicants. In addition, cast will benefit from an inclusive and enjoyable on-set experience, as well as potential exposure should the film be submitted to festivals in the future. This opportunity is particularly well suited to those who are new to the industry and looking to build or expand their showreel.

**How to Apply:**
Please email a **headshot or recent photo** and your **showreel or performance clips** (if available) to ReeseODonnell6@gmail.com and 30508450@cityofglacol.ac.uk with the subject:

“**Oneirophobia – [Character Name] – [Your Name]**”

Application deadline is **21:30**, **8th February 2026.**

Audition sides will be provided on call back.

We guarantee a professional, respectful, enjoyable, and collaborative set and would love to have you on the team.

We look forward to hearing from you!

items.text:
**Castingaufruf für studentischen Kurzfilm (Tübinale)**

Meine studentische Filmgruppe sucht Darsteller*innen für einen ca. 6-minütigen Kurzfilm, der im Rahmen der Tübinale entsteht. Gedreht wird in der Fildergegend nahe Stuttgart. Der genaue Drehzeitraum wird noch bekannt gegeben.

**Logline:**
Als eine junge Frau beginnt, ihre Beziehung mit einem anderen Paar zu vergleichen, verliert sie den Blick für die Liebe, die direkt vor ihr steht.

**Gesuchte Rollen (alle ca. 19–25 Jahre):**

**Weibliche Hauptrolle**
Junge Frau in ihrer ersten ernsthaften Beziehung. Unsicher, emotional offen, stark von äußeren Erwartungen und Vergleichen beeinflusst. Die Rolle erfordert ein sensibles Spiel innerer Konflikte und leiser emotionaler Veränderungen.

**Männliche Hauptrolle**
Ihr Freund. Bodenständig, ruhig und bemüht. Er liebt ehrlich, gerät aber zunehmend unter Druck, weil er den Erwartungen seiner Partnerin nicht gerecht werden kann. Subtiles, zurückgenommenes Spiel ist wichtig.

**Weibliche Nebenrolle**
Junge Frau mit perfekter Außenwirkung. Kontrolliert und diszipliniert, privat jedoch angespannt. Die Rolle lebt vom Kontrast zwischen äußerer Kontrolle und innerer Unsicherheit.

**Männliche Nebenrolle**
Charismatisch, dominant, stark auf Außenwirkung bedacht. Kontrollierend und schnell reizbar. Muss zwischen Charme und unterschwelliger Bedrohlichkeit wechseln können.

Schauspielerfahrung ist willkommen, aber keine Voraussetzung. Wichtig sind Verlässlichkeit, Lust auf Spielen und Interesse an einem emotionalen, beziehungszentrierten Stoff.
Bei Interesse einfach eine Nachricht schreiben, dann schicken wir weitere Infos und das Drehbuch.

items.text:
Hallo in die Runde!

Wir drehen unseren zweiten Kurzfilm “Cry Sam” und suchen hierfür den passenden Cast.

Insgesamt zu vergeben sind 4 Rollen, davon 

3 männliche Hauptrollen (Ben, Nick & Frank) sowie
1 männliche Nebenrolle (Pablo).

Worum geht’s im Film?
Ben und Nick sitzen in der Klemme. Sie haben den Banküberfall wie geplant durchgezogen aber am vereinbarten Treffpunkt taucht niemand auf. Mit zwei Geiseln an der Backe müssen sie feststellen, 
dass Geld nicht alle ihre Probleme löst.

Die genauen Rollenbeschreibungen, sowie weitere Infos zu unserem Projekt findet ihr im angehängten PDF.

Voraussichtlicher Drehzeitraum ist die zweite Oktoberwoche 2026.
Drehort ist der Neckar-Odenwaldkreis.

Es handelt sich um ein No-Budget-Projekt, Verpflegung am Set ist vorhanden, leider können wir keine Fahrtkosten und Unterkunft zahlen.

items.summary:
Hallo in die Runde!

Wir drehen unseren zweiten Kurzfilm “Cry Sam” und suchen hierfür den passenden Cast.

Insgesamt zu vergeben sind 4 Rollen, davon 

3 männliche Hauptrollen (Ben, Nick & Frank) sowie
1 männliche Nebenrolle (Pablo).

Worum geht’s im Film?
Ben und Nick sitzen in der Klemme. Sie haben den Banküberfall wie geplant durchgezogen aber am vereinbarten Treffpunkt taucht niemand auf. Mit zwei Geiseln an der Backe müssen sie feststellen, 
dass Geld nicht alle ihre Probleme löst.

Die genauen Rollenbeschreibungen, sowie weitere Infos zu unserem Projekt findet ihr im angehängten PDF.

Voraussichtlicher Drehzeitraum ist die zweite Oktoberwoche 2026.
Drehort ist der Neckar-Odenwaldkreis.

Es handelt sich um ein No-Budget-Projekt, Verpflegung am Set ist vorhanden, leider können wir keine Fahrtkosten und Unterkunft zahlen.

Meldet euch gerne direkt per Nachricht oder auch per Mail an katlenafilm@gmail.com

🎥 **Vi søger en frisk mandlig statist hos Shifa Massage!** 🌿

Vil du være med i nogle korte, videoklip til vores markedsføring, og samtidig blive forkælet med en **gratis massagebehandling**?

Vi leder efter **én mand**, der har lyst til at hjælpe os med at vise, hvad vi tilbyder i klinikken. Du skal ikke spille skuespil, bare ligge afslappet på briksen og være med i nogle stemningsfulde scener, hvor vi demonstrerer massage, udstrækning og lignende teknikker.

🎁 **Som tak får du 60 minutters valgfri professionel massage – værdi 550 kr.**

📌 Det praktiske:
– Optagelserne varer ca. 30-45 min
– Finder sted i klinikken på **Mossøvej 2, 8240 Risskov**
– Vi planlægger det, så det passer ind i din kalender
– Du skal være tryg ved videoer bliver brugt i vores markedsføring

🧴 Det eneste, vi beder om:
– En ren og præsentabel ryg/skuldre
– En rolig energi og lyst til at hjælpe
– At du er 100 % ok med at blive filmet

🎯 *Vil du være ham, der både hjælper og høster velvære?*

Send en besked, eller peg på den rette person i dit netværk.

Det kræver kun lidt tid – og du går herfra med både tak og total afslapning. 🙏✨

**CASTING SHOUT-OUT — FEATURE ARTISTS (60+)**

We’re seeking two brilliant character actors (playing age 60+) to appear as a playful “Romeo & Juliet” duo in the spirit of Compo & Nora Batty (Last of the Summer Wine) for a one-day scene in our Yorkshire-based feature film. This cameo will with our main cast, a handful of lines each, and plenty of cheeky northern charm.

**Details**

Roles:** “Romeo” & “Juliet” (feature artists, a few lines each)
Vibe:** Warm, witty, gently combative banter, think mismatched soulmates with decades of history, twinkle in the eye and spark in the step
Equity** rates (Feature Artist)
Shoot Window:** **Third week of February** (one day)

**To apply (ASAP):**

* Email kathryn@bad-fox.com with subject: **“ROMEO/JULIET — YOUR NAME — 60+”**
* Include: Spotlight link or CV, headshot(s), short reel (comedy welcome), location/postcode, availability for the **third week of February**
* Please note if you are 1 hour of Bridlington**

* We welcome submissions from all backgrounds and encourage local talent.
* Finalists may be asked for a short self-tape 

This is a joyful, good-humoured day on set, come have a laugh and steal the scene! 🎬

items.text:
Casting Call for student film🎭🎬
Comedy short film - 10 minutes 

A struggling theater show is made worse by a new member of the crew who’s inexperience makes it a night to remember.

Lee (male 20-30)

An ambitious theatre worker who is always wanting more out of life. Can be naive to the ways of the world but has blind optimism that gets him

through stressful times.

George (male 20-30)

A sarcastic, hardworking tech worker who struggles to find joy from his work. Wants to use his talents elsewhere but has no motivation to do so.

Jamie (female 25-35)

The theatre plays stressed out director who struggles with the demand of the actors and lack of backstage crew.

Expenses paid only

Shoot date: 12th-17th March 2026

Location: Aylesbury 

If interested contact: ruth.merry@outlook.com

🌟 Casting Call: Circus Performers & Professional Drummers 🌟

Are you ready to showcase your talent on an international stage? We are looking for extraordinary performers from Ukraine and Russia to join a massive month-long festival starting right after Ramadan!

We are searching for:

• Circus Artists & Stilt Walkers: High-energy performers, specifically those skilled in Giant/Stilt costumes (Giant Walkers).

• Professional Drumming Groups: High-impact, rhythmic, and visually engaging teams.

What We Provide (Fully Covered):

✅ Duration: Full 1-month contract (Post-Ramadan Festival).

✅ Travel: Round-trip Flight Tickets included.

✅ Visa: All Visa processing and costs covered by the company.

✅ Accommodation: High-quality housing provided for the duration of the festival.

How to Apply:

If you are ready for an unforgettable experience in a vibrant atmosphere, we want to see your work!

🟢 Send your Portfolio & Performance Videos via WhatsApp to:

📱 +966 58 210 1280

📍 Subject Line: [Your Name/Group Name] - Philostrad

Note: Priority will be given to performers with ready-to-use costumes and international experience.

#CircusJobs #ArtistsUkraine #ArtistsRussia #StiltWalkers #Drummers #InternationalCasting #FestivalPerformers #WorkAbroad #Philostrad

My heart is heavy as I write this.
My dear uncle, a devoted family man and a beloved member of his community, has recently moved into a nursing home. Saying goodbye to the home he built over so many years has been incredibly difficult for all of us.

Now we're facing the bittersweet task of downsizing his belongings. These aren't just things, they're pieces of a life well lived. Each item holds a memory, a story, a moment of joy. Our sincere hope is that these treasures find new homes where they'll be just as loved and appreciated as they were by him.

To help make this transition as smooth as possible, we're offering the items below on a first-come, first-serve basis.

🚨 Important Info About Reservations:

I'll be out of town assisting with his move and returning Wednesday. If you'd like to reserve an item, a deposit is required to hold it until I return and you're able to see it in person.

All deposits are 100% refundable if you decide not to move forward after viewing the item.

If you'd like more information on a specific item or how the deposit works, feel free to message me here directly.

📦Items Available:
🚗Vehicles：
 •   2018 Toyota Camry - $3,000
 •   2019 GMC sierra 1500- $7,000

 •   2021 Toyota RAV4 - $5,000

. Zero turn(BadBoyMower): $1000
 •   Side-by-Side - $2,000

 •   Honda Generator EU7000 - $800

🚛Trailers:
 •   Open Trailer - $1000
 •   Enclosed Trailer - $1,250
🏡 Home & Furniture:
 •   Bed Frame w/ Mattress - $300
 •   Refrigerator - $600
 •   Washer & Dryer - $500

🎮Other Items:
 •   Peloton Bike - $300
 •   Hot Tub - $1,000

 •   IPad Pro 2024 13inch 256GB $200
 •   Play house $500

🙏 Thank you for helping us honor my uncle's legacy by finding new homes for these cherished items. Please don't hesitate to message me with any questions about what's listed.

items.text:
## 🌵 CASTING CALL: "DEAD OR ALIVE" (SAG Short Film / Western) 🌵

Seeking lead talent for an upcoming SAG-AFTRA short film shooting in **Agua Dulce, CA**. We are looking for two powerhouse actors to lead this gritty, character-driven Western.

**PAY:** $200/day + Copy, Credit, and Meals. 

**SHOOT DATES:** February 21st & 22nd, 2026. 
IMDB: [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt39387683](https://www.imdb.com/title/tt39387683)
Director: Nick Montalvo 
Producer: 

📆 UPDATED DEADLINES & AUDITIONS 
* **SUBMISSION DEADLINE:** Monday, Feb 9th, 2026 @ 10:00 PM.
* **IN-PERSON AUDITIONS:** Wednesday, Feb 11th, 2026.
* **LOCATION:** Los Angeles / The Valley (NoHo/Studio City area).
🎭 ROLES

**[WESLEY] – LEAD** Male, 30-45. A hardened lawman who's fallen onto desperate times. Steadfast and no-nonsense. He hides his emotions well but is determined to right the world’s wrongs at all costs. We meet him as a weary man.

**[FRANCIS] – LEAD** Male, 25-35. A dangerous outlaw and Wesley's estranged younger brother. Unpredictable, brash, and uneasy. Behind the tough exterior is a hurt kid desperate to keep everyone out.

**STORYLINE:** A disgraced Sheriff seeks help from his estranged outlawed younger brother to save his ailing daughter, but intentions on both sides are not what they seem.

📩 

**DO NOT DM headshots or reels.** To be considered, please email your materials to the address below. If you are a fit for the role, you will receive a reply with **SIDES** for the audition.

**EMAIL:** ClassicalCastings@gmail.com **SUBJECT:** [Role Name] - [Your Name] - Dead or Alive

Please include your headshot, resume, and a link to your reel/work samples.

Thanks in advance! 
Spencer, 
Producer

Hi all!
I’m actively looking for work between the Northcote / Melbourne CBD area. I’m reliable, motivated, and happy to consider a range of roles.

I have over 7 years experience in customer service, am flexible with working both by myself and in a team. From entertainment (acting gigs and events and party hosting), retail, sales, driving (deliveries and people) cleaning, bar tending and last but definitely not least I have lots of management experience (specialising in quality of service and stock) my Cert IV in Hospitality and Tourism was very helpful in making my resume so colourful. I am not fussy, love learning new roles and looking to start soon. 

Feel free to comment or message me if you know of any opportunities or have any questions. 
Thanks in advance!

CASTING CALL - BRIGHTON 🎬 16+ MALE ACTOR WANTED
We’re casting for BITE, a MET Film graduate short film, and we’re looking for a local 16+ actor to join our cast!

ABOUT THE FILM

When Kev Mullen gets sacked from his job, 14-year-old Billy and loyal staffy, Ruby, are forced to bear the brunt of his father’s downfall. Led by Billy’s narration, BITE follows the attempt to navigate his father’s increasing alcoholism, volatility, and ostracisation. The screenplay has already been praised by screenwriter Rob Williams and we are hoping for big things with this film.

THE ROLE - ‘OLDER BOY’

A rough schoolmate who gives Billy and his dog a hard time. 

• Paid according to equity guidelines

WE’RE LOOKING FOR:

• Male actor, 16+

• Brighton-based

• One day of filming during the week of the 16th February

To apply, please email 1195873@sfsstudents.ac.uk with your headshots/picture. No previous experience required. Thank you! 🎥

items.text:
## 🌵 CASTING CALL: "DEAD OR ALIVE" (SAG Short Film / Western) 🌵

Seeking lead talent for an upcoming SAG-AFTRA short film shooting in **Agua Dulce, CA**. We are looking for two powerhouse actors to lead this gritty, character-driven Western.

**PAY:** $200/day + Copy, Credit, and Meals. 

**SHOOT DATES:** February 21st & 22nd, 2026. 
IMDB: [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt39387683](https://www.imdb.com/title/tt39387683)
Director: Nick Montalvo 
Producer: 

📆 UPDATED DEADLINES & AUDITIONS 
* **SUBMISSION DEADLINE:** Monday, Feb 9th, 2026 @ 10:00 PM.
* **IN-PERSON AUDITIONS:** Wednesday, Feb 11th, 2026.
* **LOCATION:** Los Angeles / The Valley (NoHo/Studio City area).
🎭 ROLES

**[WESLEY] – LEAD** Male, 30-45. A hardened lawman who's fallen onto desperate times. Steadfast and no-nonsense. He hides his emotions well but is determined to right the world’s wrongs at all costs. We meet him as a weary man.

**[FRANCIS] – LEAD** Male, 25-35. A dangerous outlaw and Wesley's estranged younger brother. Unpredictable, brash, and uneasy. Behind the tough exterior is a hurt kid desperate to keep everyone out.

**STORYLINE:** A disgraced Sheriff seeks help from his estranged outlawed younger brother to save his ailing daughter, but intentions on both sides are not what they seem.

📩 

**DO NOT DM headshots or reels.** To be considered, please email your materials to the address below. If you are a fit for the role, you will receive a reply with **SIDES** for the audition.

**EMAIL:** ClassicalCastings@gmail.com **SUBJECT:** [Role Name] - [Your Name] - Dead or Alive

Please include your headshot, resume, and a link to your reel/work samples.

Thanks in advance! 
Spencer, 
Producer

items.text:
I’m an Executive Producer building a **small, reliable team** to create content consistently with the goal of turning that work into **paid opportunities** with businesses and brands.

To be clear: my title doesn’t mean I’m throwing money at people. I’m looking for creatives who are willing to **invest in themselves**, show up, and build leverage through real work. This is a **team effort** — the work we create together is what opens doors.

If pitching or outreach isn’t your strength yet, we can align through a workshop. The goal is shared success, not gatekeeping.

If you’re ready to level up, I’ll make sure you’re positioned for more opportunities and growth — **but we move as a team**.

If this resonates, comment or DM. If not, clarity saves us both time.

items.text:
PAID OPPORTUNITY
We are casting an actress (35-45 playing age) for the role of Janice in our 10-minute student short film Elvis Died for This.

Set in 1985, the Wright family are barely holding it together. When the youngest son, Mikey, accidentally blows up their neighbour's beloved guinea pig, Elvis, in a homemade science experiment, the family scrambles to cover it up. As the chaos unravels, Mikey finally tells the truth - about the guinea pig, and about how broken his family really is. His honesty forces everyone to face reality, and the Wrights finally stop pretending to be a happy family.

No prior acting experience is required, so if this is something you are interested in, please do not hesitate to apply.

Shooting dates:

7/03/2026

14/03/2026

21/03/2026

22/03/2026

Applicants must be based in or near Falmouth, or close enough to travel to and from Falmouth each shooting weekend.

To apply or for more information email - eb300109@falmouth.ac.uk

items.text:
**CASTING CALL: PROFESSOR WILLARD**

**Supporting Role | SCAD Senior Thesis Film // *****Opulence***

**March 5-8th, 2026 | Savannah, GA**

**Logline: **

When a Black woman becomes exhausted by passive-aggressive racism at her college, she finds inspiration and connection through a myth of Black angels sent by God.

**Professor Willard (Late 30’s-50’s, White, Male):** 

A public speaking professor at Grove Technical College for five years, originally from a small town in Michigan, now living in the DMV after relocating for his wife, Iyla (African American), who works in D.C. Willard is passionate, articulate, and well-meaning; he teaches with enthusiasm, mentors his students, and doesn’t tolerate disrespect, yet struggles to speak up publicly when racism and microaggressions arise. He privately supports Myra but hesitates within institutional systems. Outside of work, he enjoys quiet nights with his wife, debating over coffee (one sugar), and taking samba classes on Tuesday nights. The role explores the tension between genuine allyship and passive complicity; not a white savior.

**Contact:**

Producer | Hannah Ballard // hballard9hb@gmail.com

Director | Music Miranda // mmiran21@student.scad.edu

*Please submit a headshot and resumé via email for more information.  *

*credit & copy of the film comp.

items.text:
Title: Saturdays

Genre: Thriller/Comedy

Logline: After accidentally taking a new designer drug on the way to a Halloween party, three broke nobodies become viral vigilantes in a city on the edge but their rise to infamy puts them in the cross-hairs of a charismatic cartel leader.

Role:

Dave (30-50) Unkillable, unshakable, and possibly unmedicated. Somehow still endearing. Dave is an uber driver, a hype man, and a secret weapon and comes from a different era. He’s the uncle at thanksgiving that you hope didn’t bring a bottle of scotch (you know he did). A chaotic wildcard who might be a genius... or just very, very lucky.

Production Type: Indie

Production Company: Loste Films

Contact Information: [luke@lostefilms.com](mailto:luke@lostefilms.com)

Run Time: Feature

Compensation: Catering/Crafty provided during proof of concept shoot. Compensation for future shoot dates is open to negotiation.

Audition Information: Send an email with headshot, resume and reel. The first round of auditions will be self-tape, then we will have in-person callbacks (downtown Denver area).

Shooting Schedule: Late February. Other shoot dates TBD

Filming Location: Highlands Ranch and Denver area

Project Description: Saturdays is an upcoming feature film we’re currently shooting the beginning of to use as a proof of concept. The scenes in the proof of concept are still being used in the final movie, which will be shot later on in the year. Due to scheduling conflicts we had to recast this role and are looking for someone who can carry mystery, comedy, and spiritual invincibility. There’s also lots of room for improv in the role. Some character inspirations include Erlich Eachman (Silicon Valley), Frank Reynolds (It’s Always Sunny), Red (Pineapple Express), Jay (Clerks), The Dude (The Big Lebowski). Attached pictures are the location/vehicles we have locked in for the first scene you’ll be shooting with us.

IMDB Link: [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt39423188/](https://www.imdb.com/title/tt39423188/)

items.text:
CASTING CALL – DRAMATIC SHORT FILM

Project Title: When the Light Fades
Type: Independent Short Film (Drama / Psychological Realism)
Production Dates: February 21st & 22nd 
Location: Denver, CO 
Compensation: $1,000 Total + IMDb Credit + Footage for Reel

SYNOPSIS
When the Light Fades is an intimate portrait of resilience and regret in a town on the brink of collapse.
After a local factory shutdown upends their lives, three young adults must face the truths they’ve spent years avoiding  about love, loyalty, and the silent compromises that shape who we become.
Through quiet moments and raw confrontation, the film explores what it means to hold onto hope when everything around you is falling apart.

ROLES NEEDED

LEAD ROLES
ARIA (Female, 19–23, Any Ethnicity)
A talented photographer caring for her sick mother. Driven yet conflicted, she’s torn between duty and the life she dreams of. Vulnerability and quiet strength define her journey.

MARCUS (Male, 20–24, Any Ethnicity)
A loyal factory worker hiding the truth about the plant’s closure. His calm exterior masks deep guilt and fear of failure. Must convey emotional restraint and inner turmoil.

NIA (Female, 18–22, Any Ethnicity)
A passionate former student activist returning home disillusioned. Restless, outspoken, and emotionally volatile. She challenges others  and herself to confront uncomfortable realities.

SUPPORTING ROLES
ZOE (Female, 17–20, Any Ethnicity)
Marcus’s younger sister. Sharp and perceptive beyond her age. She sees the fractures the older characters can’t and forces them to confront uncomfortable truths.

MRS. JACOBS (Female, 60s–70s, Any Ethnicity)
A retired teacher and quiet pillar of the community. Offers grounded wisdom and emotional perspective amid the chaos.

TO SUBMIT
Please email the following materials to everlastfilming@gmail.com 
Current headshot
Acting résumé or demo reel (if available)
Role(s) you’re submitting for
City of residence
